405 static void
406 ev_window_update_actions_sensitivity (EvWindow *ev_window)
407 {
408  EvDocument *document = ev_window->priv->document;
409  EvView *view = EV_VIEW (ev_window->priv->view);
410  const EvDocumentInfo *info = NULL;
411  gboolean has_document = FALSE;
412  gboolean ok_to_print = TRUE;
413  gboolean ok_to_copy = TRUE;
414  gboolean has_properties = TRUE;
415  gboolean override_restrictions = TRUE;
416  gboolean can_get_text = FALSE;
417  gboolean can_find = FALSE;
418  gboolean can_find_in_page;
419  gboolean can_annotate = FALSE;
420  gboolean presentation_mode;
421  gboolean recent_view_mode;
422  gboolean dual_mode = FALSE;
423  gboolean has_pages = FALSE;
424  int n_pages = 0, page = -1;
425 
426  if (document) {
427  has_document = TRUE;
428  info = ev_document_get_info (document);
429  page = ev_document_model_get_page (ev_window->priv->model);
430  n_pages = ev_document_get_n_pages (ev_window->priv->document);
431  has_pages = n_pages > 0;
432  dual_mode = ev_document_model_get_dual_page (ev_window->priv->model);
433  }
434 
435  if (!info || info->fields_mask == 0) {
436  has_properties = FALSE;
437  }
438 
439  if (has_document && EV_IS_SELECTION (document)) {
440  can_get_text = TRUE;
441  }
442 
443  if (has_pages && EV_IS_DOCUMENT_FIND (document)) {
444  can_find = TRUE;
445  }
446 
447  if (has_document && EV_IS_DOCUMENT_ANNOTATIONS (document)) {
448  can_annotate = ev_document_annotations_can_add_annotation (EV_DOCUMENT_ANNOTATIONS (document));
449  }
450 
451  if (has_document && ev_window->priv->settings) {
452  override_restrictions =
453  g_settings_get_boolean (ev_window->priv->settings,
454  GS_OVERRIDE_RESTRICTIONS);
455  }
456 
457  if (!override_restrictions && info && info->fields_mask & EV_DOCUMENT_INFO_PERMISSIONS) {
458  ok_to_print = (info->permissions & EV_DOCUMENT_PERMISSIONS_OK_TO_PRINT);
459  ok_to_copy = (info->permissions & EV_DOCUMENT_PERMISSIONS_OK_TO_COPY);
460  }
461 
462  if (has_document && !ev_print_operation_exists_for_document(document))
463  ok_to_print = FALSE;
464 
465  if (has_document && ev_window->priv->lockdown_settings &&
466  g_settings_get_boolean (ev_window->priv->lockdown_settings, GS_LOCKDOWN_SAVE)) {
467  ok_to_copy = FALSE;
468  }
469 
470  if (has_document && ev_window->priv->lockdown_settings &&
471  g_settings_get_boolean (ev_window->priv->lockdown_settings, GS_LOCKDOWN_PRINT)) {
472  ok_to_print = FALSE;
473  }
474 
475  /* Get modes */
476  presentation_mode = EV_WINDOW_IS_PRESENTATION (ev_window);
477  recent_view_mode = ev_window_is_recent_view (ev_window);
478 
479  /* File menu */
480  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "open-copy", has_document);
481  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "save-copy", has_document &&
482  ok_to_copy && !recent_view_mode);
483  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "print", has_pages &&
484  ok_to_print && !recent_view_mode);
485  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "show-properties",
486  has_document && has_properties &&
487  !recent_view_mode);
488  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "open-containing-folder",
489  has_document && !recent_view_mode);
490  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "send-to", has_document &&
491  ev_window->priv->has_mailto_handler &&
492  nautilus_sendto &&
493  !recent_view_mode);
494  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "fullscreen",
495  has_document && !recent_view_mode);
496  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "presentation",
497  has_document && !recent_view_mode);
498 
499  /* Edit menu */
500  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "select-all", has_pages &&
501  can_get_text && !recent_view_mode);
502  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "find", can_find &&
503  !recent_view_mode);
504  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "toggle-find", can_find &&
505  !recent_view_mode);
506  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "toggle-edit-annots", can_annotate &&
507  !recent_view_mode);
508  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "rotate-left", has_pages &&
509  !recent_view_mode);
510  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "rotate-right", has_pages &&
511  !recent_view_mode);
512 
513  /* View menu */
514  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "continuous", has_pages &&
515  !recent_view_mode);
516  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "dual-page", has_pages &&
517  !recent_view_mode);
518  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "dual-odd-left", has_pages &&
519  !recent_view_mode);
520  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "reload", has_pages &&
521  !recent_view_mode);
522  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "auto-scroll", has_pages &&
523  !recent_view_mode);
524  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "inverted-colors",
525  has_pages && !recent_view_mode);
526 
527  /* Bookmarks menu */
528  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "add-bookmark",
529  has_pages && ev_window->priv->bookmarks &&
530  !recent_view_mode);
531 
532  /* Other actions that must be disabled in recent view, in
533  * case they have a shortcut or gesture associated
534  */
535  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "save-settings", !recent_view_mode);
536  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "show-side-pane", !recent_view_mode);
537  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "goto-bookmark", !recent_view_mode);
538  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "scroll-forward", !recent_view_mode);
539  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "scroll-backwards", !recent_view_mode);
540  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "sizing-mode", !recent_view_mode);
541  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "zoom", !recent_view_mode);
542  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "escape", !recent_view_mode);
543  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "open-menu", !recent_view_mode);
544 
545  /* Same for popups specific actions */
546  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "open-link", !recent_view_mode);
547  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "open-link-new-window", !recent_view_mode);
548  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-to-link", !recent_view_mode);
549  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "copy-link-address", !recent_view_mode);
550  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "save-image", !recent_view_mode);
551  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "copy-image", !recent_view_mode);
552  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "open-attachment", !recent_view_mode);
553  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "save-attachment", !recent_view_mode);
554  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "annot-properties", !recent_view_mode);
555  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "remove-annot", !recent_view_mode);
556 
557  can_find_in_page = ev_search_box_has_results (EV_SEARCH_BOX (ev_window->priv->search_box));
558 
559  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "copy",
560  has_pages &&
561  ev_view_get_has_selection (view) &&
562  !recent_view_mode);
563  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "find-next",
564  has_pages && can_find_in_page &&
565  !recent_view_mode);
566  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "find-previous",
567  has_pages && can_find_in_page &&
568  !recent_view_mode);
569  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "dual-odd-left", dual_mode &&
570  !recent_view_mode);
571 
572  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "zoom-in",
573  has_pages &&
574  ev_view_can_zoom_in (view) &&
575  !presentation_mode &&
576  !recent_view_mode);
577  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "zoom-out",
578  has_pages &&
579  ev_view_can_zoom_out (view) &&
580  !presentation_mode &&
581  !recent_view_mode);
582 
583  /* Go menu */
584  if (has_pages) {
585  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-previous-page", page > 0);
586  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-next-page", page < n_pages - 1);
587  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-first-page", page > 0);
588  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-last-page", page < n_pages - 1);
589  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "select-page", TRUE);
590  } else {
591  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-first-page", FALSE);
592  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-previous-page", FALSE);
593  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-next-page", FALSE);
594  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-last-page", FALSE);
595  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "select-page", FALSE);
596  }
597 
598  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-back-history",
599  !ev_history_is_frozen (ev_window->priv->history) &&
600  ev_history_can_go_back (ev_window->priv->history) &&
601  !recent_view_mode);
602  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "go-forward-history",
603  !ev_history_is_frozen (ev_window->priv->history) &&
604  ev_history_can_go_forward (ev_window->priv->history) &&
605  !recent_view_mode);
606 
607  ev_window_set_action_enabled (ev_window, "caret-navigation",
608  has_pages &&
609  ev_view_supports_caret_navigation (view) &&
610  !presentation_mode &&
611  !recent_view_mode);
612 }

853 static const gchar *

882 static void
883 view_handle_link_cb (EvView *view, EvLink *link, EvWindow *window)
884 {

975 static const gchar *

996  id = BOOKMARKS_SIDEBAR_ID;
997  } else {

999  }
1000 
1001  g_object_unref (current_page);
1002 
1003  return id;

1006 static void
1007 ev_window_sidebar_set_current_page (EvWindow *window,
1008  const gchar *page_id)
1009 {
1010  EvDocument *document = window->priv->document;
1011  EvSidebar *sidebar = EV_SIDEBAR (window->priv->sidebar);
1012  GtkWidget *links = window->priv->sidebar_links;
1013  GtkWidget *thumbs = window->priv->sidebar_thumbs;
1014  GtkWidget *attachments = window->priv->sidebar_attachments;
1015  GtkWidget *annots = window->priv->sidebar_annots;
1016  GtkWidget *layers = window->priv->sidebar_layers;
1017  GtkWidget *bookmarks = window->priv->sidebar_bookmarks;
1018

1020  ev_sidebar_page_support_document (EV_SIDEBAR_PAGE (links), document)) {

1022  } else if (strcmp (page_id, THUMBNAILS_SIDEBAR_ID) == 0 &&
1023  ev_sidebar_page_support_document (EV_SIDEBAR_PAGE (thumbs), document)) {
1024  ev_sidebar_set_page (sidebar, thumbs);
1025  } else if (strcmp (page_id, ATTACHMENTS_SIDEBAR_ID) == 0 &&
1026  ev_sidebar_page_support_document (EV_SIDEBAR_PAGE (attachments), document)) {
1027  ev_sidebar_set_page (sidebar, attachments);
1028  } else if (strcmp (page_id, LAYERS_SIDEBAR_ID) == 0 &&
1029  ev_sidebar_page_support_document (EV_SIDEBAR_PAGE (layers), document)) {
1030  ev_sidebar_set_page (sidebar, layers);
1031  } else if (strcmp (page_id, ANNOTS_SIDEBAR_ID) == 0 &&
1032  ev_sidebar_page_support_document (EV_SIDEBAR_PAGE (annots), document)) {
1033  ev_sidebar_set_page (sidebar, annots);
1034  } else if (strcmp (page_id, BOOKMARKS_SIDEBAR_ID) == 0 &&
1035  ev_sidebar_page_support_document (EV_SIDEBAR_PAGE (bookmarks), document)) {
1036  ev_sidebar_set_page (sidebar, bookmarks);
1037  } else {
1038  /* setup thumbnails by default */
1039  ev_sidebar_set_page (sidebar, thumbs);
1040  }
1041 }

1098

1100  }
1101 
1102  if (!ev_metadata_has_key (metadata, "zoom")) {

1104  g_settings_get_double (settings, "zoom"));

1145 static void
1146 setup_model_from_metadata (EvWindow *window)
1147 {
1148  gint page;
1149  gchar *sizing_mode;
1150  gdouble zoom;
1151  gint rotation;
1152  gboolean inverted_colors = FALSE;
1153  gboolean continuous = FALSE;
1154  gboolean dual_page = FALSE;
1155  gboolean dual_page_odd_left = FALSE;
1156  gboolean fullscreen = FALSE;
1157 
1158  if (!window->priv->metadata)
1159  return;
1160 
1161  /* Current page */
1162  if (!window->priv->dest &&
1163  ev_metadata_get_int (window->priv->metadata, "page", &page)) {
1164  ev_document_model_set_page (window->priv->model, page);
1165  }
1166 
1167  /* Sizing mode */
1168  if (ev_metadata_get_string (window->priv->metadata, "sizing_mode", &sizing_mode)) {
1169  GEnumValue *enum_value;
1170 
1171  enum_value = g_enum_get_value_by_nick
1172  (g_type_class_peek (EV_TYPE_SIZING_MODE), sizing_mode);
1173  ev_document_model_set_sizing_mode (window->priv->model, enum_value->value);
1174  }
1175 
1176  /* Zoom */
1177  if (ev_document_model_get_sizing_mode (window->priv->model) == EV_SIZING_FREE) {
1178  if (ev_metadata_get_double (window->priv->metadata, "zoom", &zoom)) {
1179  zoom *= get_screen_dpi (window) / 72.0;
1180  ev_document_model_set_scale (window->priv->model, zoom);
1181  }
1182  }
1183 
1184  /* Rotation */
1185  if (ev_metadata_get_int (window->priv->metadata, "rotation", &rotation)) {
1186  switch (rotation) {
1187  case 90:
1188  rotation = 90;
1189  break;
1190  case 180:
1191  rotation = 180;
1192  break;
1193  case 270:
1194  rotation = 270;
1195  break;
1196  default:
1197  rotation = 0;
1198  break;
1199  }
1200  ev_document_model_set_rotation (window->priv->model, rotation);
1201  }
1202 
1203  /* Inverted Colors */
1204  if (ev_metadata_get_boolean (window->priv->metadata, "inverted-colors", &inverted_colors)) {
1205  ev_document_model_set_inverted_colors (window->priv->model, inverted_colors);
1206  }
1207 
1208  /* Continuous */
1209  if (ev_metadata_get_boolean (window->priv->metadata, "continuous", &continuous)) {
1210  ev_document_model_set_continuous (window->priv->model, continuous);
1211  }
1212 
1213  /* Dual page */
1214  if (ev_metadata_get_boolean (window->priv->metadata, "dual-page", &dual_page)) {
1215  ev_document_model_set_dual_page (window->priv->model, dual_page);
1216  }
1217 
1218  /* Dual page odd pages left */
1219  if (ev_metadata_get_boolean (window->priv->metadata, "dual-page-odd-left", &dual_page_odd_left)) {
1220  ev_document_model_set_dual_page_odd_pages_left (window->priv->model, dual_page_odd_left);
1221  }
1222 
1223  /* Fullscreen */
1224  if (ev_metadata_get_boolean (window->priv->metadata, "fullscreen", &fullscreen)) {
1225  if (fullscreen)
1226  ev_window_run_fullscreen (window);
1227  }
1228 }

1230 static void
1231 setup_document_from_metadata (EvWindow *window)
1232 {
1233  gint page, n_pages;
1234  gint width;
1235  gint height;
1236  gdouble width_ratio;
1237  gdouble height_ratio;
1238 
1239  if (!window->priv->metadata)
1240  return;
1241 
1242  setup_sidebar_from_metadata (window);
1243 
1244  /* Make sure to not open a document on the last page,
1245  * since closing it on the last page most likely means the
1246  * user was finished reading the document. In that case, reopening should
1247  * show the first page. */
1248  page = ev_document_model_get_page (window->priv->model);
1249  n_pages = ev_document_get_n_pages (window->priv->document);
1250  if (page == n_pages - 1)
1251  ev_document_model_set_page (window->priv->model, 0);
1252 
1253  if (ev_metadata_get_int (window->priv->metadata, "window_width", &width) &&
1254  ev_metadata_get_int (window->priv->metadata, "window_height", &height))
1255  return; /* size was already set in setup_size_from_metadata */
1256 
1257  if (n_pages == 1)
1258  ev_document_model_set_dual_page (window->priv->model, FALSE);
1259 
1260  g_settings_get (window->priv->default_settings, "window-ratio", "(dd)", &width_ratio, &height_ratio);
1261  if (width_ratio > 0. && height_ratio > 0.) {
1262  gdouble document_width;
1263  gdouble document_height;
1264  GdkScreen *screen;
1265  gint request_width;
1266  gint request_height;
1267 
1268  ev_document_get_max_page_size (window->priv->document,
1269  &document_width, &document_height);
1270 
1271  request_width = (gint)(width_ratio * document_width + 0.5);
1272  request_height = (gint)(height_ratio * document_height + 0.5);
1273 
1274  screen = gtk_window_get_screen (GTK_WINDOW (window));
1275  if (screen) {
1276  request_width = MIN (request_width, gdk_screen_get_width (screen));
1277  request_height = MIN (request_height, gdk_screen_get_height (screen));
1278  }
1279 
1280  if (request_width > 0 && request_height > 0) {
1281  gtk_window_resize (GTK_WINDOW (window),
1282  request_width,
1283  request_height);
1284  }
1285  }
1286 }

1702 
1703 /* This callback will executed when load job will be finished.
1704  *
1705  * Since the flow of the error dialog is very confusing, we assume that both
1706  * document and uri will go away after this function is called, and thus we need
1707  * to ref/dup them. Additionally, it needs to clear
1708  * ev_window->priv->password_{uri,document}, and thus people who call this
1709  * function should _not_ necessarily expect those to exist after being
1710  * called. */
1711 static void
1712 ev_window_load_job_cb (EvJob *job,
1713  gpointer data)
1714 {
1715  EvWindow *ev_window = EV_WINDOW (data);
1716  EvDocument *document = EV_JOB (job)->document;
1717  EvJobLoad *job_load = EV_JOB_LOAD (job);
1718  gchar *text;
1719  gchar *display_name;
1720 
1721  g_assert (job_load->uri);
1722 
1723  ev_window_hide_loading_message (ev_window);
1724 
1725  /* Success! */
1726  if (!ev_job_is_failed (job)) {
1727  ev_document_model_set_document (ev_window->priv->model, document);
1728 
1729 #ifdef ENABLE_DBUS
1730  ev_window_emit_doc_loaded (ev_window);
1731 #endif
1732  setup_chrome_from_metadata (ev_window);
1733  setup_document_from_metadata (ev_window);
1734  setup_view_from_metadata (ev_window);
1735 
1736  ev_window_add_recent (ev_window, ev_window->priv->uri);
1737 
1738  ev_window_title_set_type (ev_window->priv->title,
1739  EV_WINDOW_TITLE_DOCUMENT);
1740  if (job_load->password) {
1741  GPasswordSave flags;
1742 
1743  flags = ev_password_view_get_password_save_flags (
1744  EV_PASSWORD_VIEW (ev_window->priv->password_view));
1745  ev_keyring_save_password (ev_window->priv->uri,
1746  job_load->password,
1747  flags);
1748  }
1749 
1750  ev_window_handle_link (ev_window, ev_window->priv->dest);
1751  g_clear_object (&ev_window->priv->dest);
1752 
1753  switch (ev_window->priv->window_mode) {
1754  case EV_WINDOW_MODE_FULLSCREEN:
1755  ev_window_run_fullscreen (ev_window);
1756  break;
1757  case EV_WINDOW_MODE_PRESENTATION:
1758  ev_window_run_presentation (ev_window);
1759  break;
1760  default:
1761  break;
1762  }
1763 
1764  /* Create a monitor for the document */
1765  ev_window->priv->monitor = ev_file_monitor_new (ev_window->priv->uri);
1766  g_signal_connect_swapped (ev_window->priv->monitor, "changed",
1767  G_CALLBACK (ev_window_file_changed),
1768  ev_window);
1769 
1770  ev_window_clear_load_job (ev_window);
1771  return;
1772  }
1773 
1774  if (g_error_matches (job->error, EV_DOCUMENT_ERROR, EV_DOCUMENT_ERROR_ENCRYPTED)) {
1775  gchar *password;
1776 
1777  setup_view_from_metadata (ev_window);
1778 
1779  /* First look whether password is in keyring */
1780  password = ev_keyring_lookup_password (ev_window->priv->uri);
1781  if (password) {
1782  if (job_load->password && strcmp (password, job_load->password) == 0) {
1783  /* Password in kering is wrong */
1784  ev_job_load_set_password (job_load, NULL);
1785  /* FIXME: delete password from keyring? */
1786  } else {
1787  ev_job_load_set_password (job_load, password);
1788  ev_job_scheduler_push_job (job, EV_JOB_PRIORITY_NONE);
1789  g_free (password);
1790  return;
1791  }
1792 
1793  g_free (password);
1794  }
1795 
1796  /* We need to ask the user for a password */
1797  ev_window_title_set_uri (ev_window->priv->title,
1798  ev_window->priv->uri);
1799  ev_window_title_set_type (ev_window->priv->title,

2106 static void
2107 ev_window_load_file_remote (EvWindow *ev_window,
2108  GFile *source_file)
2109 {
2110  GFile *target_file;
2111 
2112  if (!ev_window->priv->local_uri) {
2113  char *base_name, *template;
2114  GFile *tmp_file;
2115  GError *err = NULL;
2116 
2117  /* We'd like to keep extension of source uri since
2118  * it helps to resolve some mime types, say cbz.
2119  */
2120  base_name = g_file_get_basename (source_file);
2121  template = g_strdup_printf ("document.XXXXXX-%s", base_name);
2122  g_free (base_name);
2123 
2124  tmp_file = ev_mkstemp_file (template, &err);
2125  g_free (template);
2126  if (tmp_file == NULL) {
2127  ev_window_error_message (ev_window, err,
2128  "%s", _("Failed to load remote file."));
2129  g_error_free (err);
2130  return;
2131  }
2132 
2133  ev_window->priv->local_uri = g_file_get_uri (tmp_file);
2134  g_object_unref (tmp_file);
2135 
2136  ev_job_load_set_uri (EV_JOB_LOAD (ev_window->priv->load_job),
2137  ev_window->priv->local_uri);
2138  }
2139 
2140  ev_window_reset_progress_cancellable (ev_window);
2141 
2142  target_file = g_file_new_for_uri (ev_window->priv->local_uri);
2143  g_file_copy_async (source_file, target_file,
2144  G_FILE_COPY_OVERWRITE,
2145  G_PRIORITY_DEFAULT,
2146  ev_window->priv->progress_cancellable,
2147  (GFileProgressCallback)window_open_file_copy_progress_cb,
2148  ev_window,
2149  (GAsyncReadyCallback)window_open_file_copy_ready_cb,
2150  ev_window);
2151  g_object_unref (target_file);
2152 
2153  ev_window_show_progress_message (ev_window, 1,
2154  (GSourceFunc)show_loading_progress);
2155 }

2438 {
2439  GFileInfo *info;
2440  GTimeVal mtime;
2441  GError *error = NULL;
2442 
2443  info = g_file_query_info_finish (remote, async_result, &error);
2444  if (error) {
2445  g_error_free (error);
2446  g_object_unref (remote);
2447  ev_window_reload_local (ev_window);
2448 
2449  return;
2450  }
2451 
2452  g_file_info_get_modification_time (info, &mtime);
2453  if (ev_window->priv->uri_mtime != mtime.tv_sec) {
2454  GFile *target_file;
2455 
2456  /* Remote file has changed */
2457  ev_window->priv->uri_mtime = mtime.tv_sec;
2458 
2459  ev_window_reset_progress_cancellable (ev_window);
2460 
2461  target_file = g_file_new_for_uri (ev_window->priv->local_uri);
2462  g_file_copy_async (remote, target_file,
2463  G_FILE_COPY_OVERWRITE,
2464  G_PRIORITY_DEFAULT,
2465  ev_window->priv->progress_cancellable,
2466  (GFileProgressCallback)reload_remote_copy_progress_cb,
2467  ev_window,
2468  (GAsyncReadyCallback)reload_remote_copy_ready_cb,
2469  ev_window);
2470  g_object_unref (target_file);
2471  ev_window_show_progress_message (ev_window, 1,
2472  (GSourceFunc)show_reloading_progress);
2473  } else {
2474  g_object_unref (remote);
2475  ev_window_reload_local (ev_window);
2476  }
2477 
2478  g_object_unref (info);
2479 }

3279 static void
3280 ev_window_print_operation_done (EvPrintOperation *op,
3281  GtkPrintOperationResult result,
3282  EvWindow *ev_window)
3283 {
3284  gint n_jobs;
3285 
3286  switch (result) {
3287  case GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_APPLY: {
3288  GtkPrintSettings *print_settings;
3289 
3290  print_settings = ev_print_operation_get_print_settings (op);
3291  ev_window_save_print_settings (ev_window, print_settings);
3292

3295

3297  ev_window_save_print_page_setup (ev_window, page_setup);

3300

3302  case GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_ERROR: {
3303  GtkWidget *dialog;
3304  GError *error = NULL;
3305 
3306 
3307  ev_print_operation_get_error (op, &error);
3308 
3309  /* The message area is already used by
3310  * the printing progress, so it's better to
3311  * use a popup dialog in this case
3312  */
3313  dialog = gtk_message_dialog_new (GTK_WINDOW (ev_window),
3314  GTK_DIALOG_DESTROY_WITH_PARENT,
3315  GTK_MESSAGE_ERROR,

3317  "%s", _("Failed to print document"));
3318  gtk_message_dialog_format_secondary_text (GTK_MESSAGE_DIALOG (dialog),
3319  "%s", error->message);
3320  g_signal_connect (dialog, "response",
3321  G_CALLBACK (gtk_widget_destroy),
3322  NULL);
3323  gtk_widget_show (dialog);
3324 
3325  g_error_free (error);
3326  }
3327  break;
3328  case GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_CANCEL:
3329  default:
3330  break;
3331  }
3332 
3333  g_queue_remove (ev_window->priv->print_queue, op);
3334  g_object_unref (op);
3335  n_jobs = g_queue_get_length (ev_window->priv->print_queue);
3336  ev_window_print_update_pending_jobs_message (ev_window, n_jobs);
3337 
3338  if (n_jobs == 0 && ev_window->priv->close_after_print)
3339  g_idle_add ((GSourceFunc)destroy_window,
3340  ev_window);
3341 }

3410 void
3411 ev_window_print_range (EvWindow *ev_window,
3412  gint first_page,
3413  gint last_page)
3414 {
3415  EvPrintOperation *op;
3416  GKeyFile *print_settings_file;
3417  GtkPrintSettings *print_settings;
3418  GtkPageSetup *print_page_setup;
3419  gint current_page;
3420  gint document_last_page;
3421  gboolean embed_page_setup;
3422  gchar *output_basename;
3423  gchar *unescaped_basename;
3424  const gchar *document_uri;
3425  gchar *dot;
3426 
3427  g_return_if_fail (EV_IS_WINDOW (ev_window));
3428  g_return_if_fail (ev_window->priv->document != NULL);
3429 
3430  if (!ev_window->priv->print_queue)
3431  ev_window->priv->print_queue = g_queue_new ();
3432 
3433  op = ev_print_operation_new (ev_window->priv->document);
3434  if (!op) {
3435  g_warning ("%s", "Printing is not supported for document\n");
3436  return;
3437  }
3438

3440  G_CALLBACK (ev_window_print_operation_begin_print),
3441  (gpointer)ev_window);

3443  G_CALLBACK (ev_window_print_operation_status_changed),

3445  g_signal_connect (op, "done",
3446  G_CALLBACK (ev_window_print_operation_done),
3447  (gpointer)ev_window);

3450  document_last_page = ev_document_get_n_pages (ev_window->priv->document);

3460  if (first_page != 1 || last_page != document_last_page) {
3461  GtkPageRange range;
3462

3464  range.start = first_page - 1;
3465  range.end = last_page - 1;
3466

3468  GTK_PRINT_PAGES_RANGES);

3640  gtk_widget_destroy (GTK_WIDGET (ev_window));
3641  else
3642  ev_window->priv->close_after_print = TRUE;
3643  break;
3644  case GTK_RESPONSE_NO:
3645  ev_window->priv->close_after_print = TRUE;
3646  if (ev_window->priv->print_queue &&
3647  !g_queue_is_empty (ev_window->priv->print_queue)) {
3648  gtk_widget_set_sensitive (GTK_WIDGET (ev_window), FALSE);
3649  ev_window_print_cancel (ev_window);
3650  } else {
3651  gtk_widget_destroy (GTK_WIDGET (ev_window));
3652  }
3653  break;
3654  case GTK_RESPONSE_CANCEL:
3655  default:
3656  ev_window->priv->close_after_print = FALSE;
3657  }
3658 }

3660 static gboolean
3661 ev_window_check_print_queue (EvWindow *ev_window)
3662 {
3663  GtkWidget *dialog;
3664  gchar *text, *markup;
3665  gint n_print_jobs;
3666 
3667  n_print_jobs = ev_window->priv->print_queue ?
3668  g_queue_get_length (ev_window->priv->print_queue) : 0;
3669 
3670  if (n_print_jobs == 0)
3671  return FALSE;
3672 
3673  dialog = gtk_message_dialog_new (GTK_WINDOW (ev_window),
3674  GTK_DIALOG_MODAL,
3675  GTK_MESSAGE_QUESTION,
3676  GTK_BUTTONS_NONE,
3677  NULL);
3678  if (n_print_jobs == 1) {
3679  EvPrintOperation *op;
3680  const gchar *job_name;
3681 
3682  op = g_queue_peek_tail (ev_window->priv->print_queue);
3683  job_name = ev_print_operation_get_job_name (op);
3684 
3685  text = g_strdup_printf (_("Wait until print job “%s” finishes before closing?"),
3686  job_name);
3687  } else {
3688  /* TRANS: the singular form is not really used as n_print_jobs > 1
3689  but some languages distinguish between different plurals forms,
3690  so the ngettext is needed. */
3691  text = g_strdup_printf (ngettext("There is %d print job active. "
3692  "Wait until print finishes before closing?",
3693  "There are %d print jobs active. "
3694  "Wait until print finishes before closing?",
3695  n_print_jobs),
3696  n_print_jobs);
3697  }
3698 
3699  markup = g_strdup_printf ("<b>%s</b>", text);
3700  g_free (text);
3701 
3702  gtk_message_dialog_set_markup (GTK_MESSAGE_DIALOG (dialog), markup);
3703  g_free (markup);
3704 
3705  gtk_message_dialog_format_secondary_text (GTK_MESSAGE_DIALOG (dialog), "%s",
3706  _("If you close the window, pending print "
3707  "jobs will not be printed."));
3708 
3709  gtk_dialog_add_buttons (GTK_DIALOG (dialog),
3710  _("Cancel _print and Close"),
3711  GTK_RESPONSE_NO,
3712  GTK_STOCK_CANCEL,
3713  GTK_RESPONSE_CANCEL,
3714  _("Close _after Printing"),
3715  GTK_RESPONSE_YES,
3716  NULL);
3717  gtk_dialog_set_default_response (GTK_DIALOG (dialog), GTK_RESPONSE_YES);
3718  gtk_dialog_set_alternative_button_order (GTK_DIALOG (dialog),
3719  GTK_RESPONSE_YES,
3720  GTK_RESPONSE_NO,
3721  GTK_RESPONSE_CANCEL,
3722  -1);
3723 
3724  g_signal_connect (dialog, "response",
3725  G_CALLBACK (print_jobs_confirmation_dialog_response),
3726  ev_window);
3727  gtk_widget_show (dialog);
3728 
3729  return TRUE;
3730 }

4294 static void
4295 ev_window_run_presentation (EvWindow *window)
4296 {
4297  gboolean fullscreen_window = TRUE;
4298  guint current_page;
4299  guint rotation;
4300  gboolean inverted_colors;
4301 
4302  if (EV_WINDOW_IS_PRESENTATION (window))
4303  return;
4304 
4305  if (ev_document_model_get_fullscreen (window->priv->model)) {
4306  ev_window_stop_fullscreen (window, FALSE);
4307  fullscreen_window = FALSE;
4308  }
4309 
4310  current_page = ev_document_model_get_page (window->priv->model);
4311  rotation = ev_document_model_get_rotation (window->priv->model);
4312  inverted_colors = ev_document_model_get_inverted_colors (window->priv->model);
4313  window->priv->presentation_view = ev_view_presentation_new (window->priv->document,
4314  current_page,
4315  rotation,
4316  inverted_colors);
4317  g_signal_connect_swapped (window->priv->presentation_view, "finished",
4318  G_CALLBACK (ev_window_view_presentation_finished),
4319  window);
4320  g_signal_connect_swapped (window->priv->presentation_view, "external-link",
4321  G_CALLBACK (view_external_link_cb),
4322  window);
4323  g_signal_connect_swapped (window->priv->presentation_view, "focus-in-event",
4324  G_CALLBACK (ev_window_view_presentation_focus_in),
4325  window);
4326  g_signal_connect_swapped (window->priv->presentation_view, "focus-out-event",
4327  G_CALLBACK (ev_window_view_presentation_focus_out),
4328  window);
4329 
4330  gtk_box_pack_start (GTK_BOX (window->priv->main_box),
4331  window->priv->presentation_view,
4332  TRUE, TRUE, 0);
4333 
4334  gtk_widget_hide (window->priv->hpaned);
4335  ev_window_update_presentation_action (window);
4336  update_chrome_visibility (window);
4337 
4338  gtk_widget_grab_focus (window->priv->presentation_view);
4339  if (fullscreen_window)
4340  gtk_window_fullscreen (GTK_WINDOW (window));
4341 
4342  gtk_widget_show (window->priv->presentation_view);
4343 
4344  ev_window_inhibit_screensaver (window);
4345 
4346  if (window->priv->metadata && !ev_window_is_empty (window))
4347  ev_metadata_set_boolean (window->priv->metadata, "presentation", TRUE);
4348 }

4350 static void
4351 ev_window_stop_presentation (EvWindow *window,
4352  gboolean unfullscreen_window)
4353 {
4354  guint current_page;
4355  guint rotation;
4356 
4357  if (!EV_WINDOW_IS_PRESENTATION (window))
4358  return;
4359 
4360  current_page = ev_view_presentation_get_current_page (EV_VIEW_PRESENTATION (window->priv->presentation_view));
4361  ev_document_model_set_page (window->priv->model, current_page);
4362  rotation = ev_view_presentation_get_rotation (EV_VIEW_PRESENTATION (window->priv->presentation_view));
4363  ev_document_model_set_rotation (window->priv->model, rotation);
4364 
4365  gtk_container_remove (GTK_CONTAINER (window->priv->main_box),
4366  window->priv->presentation_view);
4367  window->priv->presentation_view = NULL;
4368 
4369  gtk_widget_show (window->priv->hpaned);
4370  ev_window_update_presentation_action (window);
4371  update_chrome_visibility (window);
4372  if (unfullscreen_window)
4373  gtk_window_unfullscreen (GTK_WINDOW (window));
4374 
4375  gtk_widget_grab_focus (window->priv->view);
4376 
4377  ev_window_uninhibit_screensaver (window);
4378 
4379  if (window->priv->metadata && !ev_window_is_empty (window))
4380  ev_metadata_set_boolean (window->priv->metadata, "presentation", FALSE);
4381 }

4399 static gboolean
4400 ev_window_state_event (GtkWidget *widget,
4401  GdkEventWindowState *event)
4402 {
4403  EvWindow *window = EV_WINDOW (widget);
4404 
4405  if (GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (ev_window_parent_class)->window_state_event) {
4406  GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (ev_window_parent_class)->window_state_event (widget, event);
4407  }
4408 
4409  if ((event->changed_mask & GDK_WINDOW_STATE_FULLSCREEN) == 0)
4410  return FALSE;
4411 
4412  if (event->new_window_state & GDK_WINDOW_STATE_FULLSCREEN) {

4414  return FALSE;
4415

4417  } else {
4418  if (ev_document_model_get_fullscreen (window->priv->model))
4419  ev_window_stop_fullscreen (window, FALSE);
4420  else if (EV_WINDOW_IS_PRESENTATION (window))
4421  ev_window_stop_presentation (window, FALSE);
4422  }
4423 
4424  return FALSE;
4425 }

4427 static void

4430 {

4432  GtkWidget *real_child;

4434  if (window->priv->page_mode == page_mode)
4435  return;
4436 
4437  window->priv->page_mode = page_mode;
4438 
4439  switch (page_mode) {
4440  case PAGE_MODE_DOCUMENT:
4441  child = window->priv->view;
4442  break;
4443  case PAGE_MODE_PASSWORD:

4446  default:
4447  g_assert_not_reached ();
4448  }
4449 
4450  real_child = gtk_bin_get_child (GTK_BIN (window->priv->scrolled_window));
4451  if (child != real_child) {
4452  gtk_container_remove (GTK_CONTAINER (window->priv->scrolled_window),
4453  real_child);
4454  gtk_container_add (GTK_CONTAINER (window->priv->scrolled_window),
4455  child);
4456  }
4457  ev_window_update_actions_sensitivity (window);
4458 }

5615 /*
5616  * GtkWindow catches keybindings for the menu items _before_ passing them to
5617  * the focused widget. This is unfortunate and means that pressing Ctrl+a,
5618  * Ctrl+left or Ctrl+right in the search bar ends up selecting text in the EvView
5619  * or rotating it.
5620  * Here we override GtkWindow's handler to do the same things that it
5621  * does, but in the opposite order and then we chain up to the grand
5622  * parent handler, skipping gtk_window_key_press_event.
5623  */
5624 static gboolean
5625 ev_window_key_press_event (GtkWidget *widget,
5626  GdkEventKey *event)
5627 {
5628  static gpointer grand_parent_class = NULL;
5629  GtkWindow *window = GTK_WINDOW (widget);
5630 
5631  if (grand_parent_class == NULL)
5632  grand_parent_class = g_type_class_peek_parent (ev_window_parent_class);
5633 
5634  /* Handle focus widget key events */
5635  if (gtk_window_propagate_key_event (window, event))
5636  return TRUE;
5637 
5638  /* Handle mnemonics and accelerators */
5639  if (gtk_window_activate_key (window, event))
5640  return TRUE;
5641 
5642  /* Chain up, invokes binding set on window */
5643  return GTK_WIDGET_CLASS (grand_parent_class)->key_press_event (widget, event);
5644 }

5651 }

5886 static void
5887 launch_action (EvWindow *window, EvLinkAction *action)
5888 {
5889  const char *filename = ev_link_action_get_filename (action);
5890  GAppInfo *app_info;
5891  GFile *file;
5892  GList file_list = {NULL};
5893  GdkAppLaunchContext *context;
5894  GdkScreen *screen;
5895  GError *error = NULL;
5896 
5897  if (filename == NULL)
5898  return;
5899 
5900  if (g_path_is_absolute (filename)) {
5901  file = g_file_new_for_path (filename);
5902  } else {
5903  GFile *base_file;
5904  gchar *dir;
5905 
5906  dir = g_path_get_dirname (window->priv->uri);
5907  base_file = g_file_new_for_uri (dir);
5908  g_free (dir);
5909 
5910  file = g_file_resolve_relative_path (base_file, filename);
5911  g_object_unref (base_file);
5912  }
5913 
5914  app_info = g_file_query_default_handler (file, NULL, &error);
5915  if (!app_info) {
5916  ev_window_error_message (window, error,
5917  "%s",
5918  _("Unable to launch external application."));
5919  g_object_unref (file);
5920  g_error_free (error);
5921 
5922  return;
5923  }
5924 
5925  screen = gtk_window_get_screen (GTK_WINDOW (window));
5926  context = gdk_display_get_app_launch_context (gdk_screen_get_display (screen));
5927  gdk_app_launch_context_set_screen (context, screen);
5928  gdk_app_launch_context_set_timestamp (context, gtk_get_current_event_time ());
5929 
5930  file_list.data = file;
5931  if (!g_app_info_launch (app_info, &file_list, G_APP_LAUNCH_CONTEXT (context), &error)) {
5932  ev_window_error_message (window, error,
5933  "%s",
5934  _("Unable to launch external application."));
5935  g_error_free (error);
5936  }
5937 
5938  g_object_unref (app_info);
5939  g_object_unref (file);
5940  /* FIXMEchpe: unref launch context? */
5941 
5942  /* According to the PDF spec filename can be an executable. I'm not sure
5943  allowing to launch executables is a good idea though. -- marco */
5944 }

5946 static void
5947 launch_external_uri (EvWindow *window, EvLinkAction *action)
5948 {
5949  const gchar *uri = ev_link_action_get_uri (action);
5950  GError *error = NULL;
5951  gboolean ret;
5952  GdkAppLaunchContext *context;
5953  GdkScreen *screen;
5954 
5955  screen = gtk_window_get_screen (GTK_WINDOW (window));
5956  context = gdk_display_get_app_launch_context (gdk_screen_get_display (screen));
5957  gdk_app_launch_context_set_screen (context, screen);
5958  gdk_app_launch_context_set_timestamp (context, gtk_get_current_event_time ());
5959 
5960  if (!g_strstr_len (uri, strlen (uri), "://") &&
5961  !g_str_has_prefix (uri, "mailto:")) {
5962  gchar *new_uri;
5963 
5964  /* Not a valid uri, assume http if it starts with www */
5965  if (g_str_has_prefix (uri, "www.")) {
5966  new_uri = g_strdup_printf ("http://%s", uri);
5967  } else {
5968  GFile *file, *parent;
5969 
5970  file = g_file_new_for_uri (window->priv->uri);
5971  parent = g_file_get_parent (file);
5972  g_object_unref (file);
5973  if (parent) {
5974  gchar *parent_uri = g_file_get_uri (parent);
5975 
5976  new_uri = g_build_filename (parent_uri, uri, NULL);
5977  g_free (parent_uri);
5978  g_object_unref (parent);
5979  } else {
5980  new_uri = g_strdup_printf ("file:///%s", uri);
5981  }
5982  }
5983  ret = g_app_info_launch_default_for_uri (new_uri, G_APP_LAUNCH_CONTEXT (context), &error);
5984  g_free (new_uri);
5985  } else {
5986  ret = g_app_info_launch_default_for_uri (uri, G_APP_LAUNCH_CONTEXT (context), &error);
5987  }
5988 
5989  if (ret == FALSE) {
5990  ev_window_error_message (window, error,
5991  "%s", _("Unable to open external link"));
5992  g_error_free (error);
5993  }
5994 
5995  /* FIXMEchpe: unref launch context? */
5996 }

6021 do_action_named (EvWindow *window, EvLinkAction *action)
6022 {
6023  const gchar *name = ev_link_action_get_name (action);
6024 
6025  if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (name, "FirstPage") == 0) {
6026  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "go-first-page", NULL);
6027  } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (name, "PrevPage") == 0) {
6028  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "go-previous-page", NULL);
6029  } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (name, "NextPage") == 0) {
6030  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "go-next-page", NULL);
6031  } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (name, "LastPage") == 0) {
6032  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "go-last-page", NULL);
6033  } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (name, "GoToPage") == 0) {
6034  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "select-page", NULL);
6035  } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (name, "Find") == 0) {
6036  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "find", NULL);
6037  } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (name, "Close") == 0) {
6038  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "close", NULL);
6039  } else if (g_ascii_strcasecmp (name, "Print") == 0) {
6040  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "print", NULL);
6041  } else {
6042  g_warning ("Unimplemented named action: %s, please post a "
6043  "bug report in Evince bugzilla "
6044  "(http://bugzilla.gnome.org) with a testcase.",
6045  name);
6046  }
6047 }

6126 static GFile *
6127 create_file_from_uri_for_format (const gchar *uri,
6128  GdkPixbufFormat *format)
6129 {
6130  GFile *target_file;
6131  gchar **extensions;
6132  gchar *uri_extension;
6133  gint i;
6134 
6135  extensions = gdk_pixbuf_format_get_extensions (format);
6136  for (i = 0; extensions[i]; i++) {
6137  if (g_str_has_suffix (uri, extensions[i])) {
6138  g_strfreev (extensions);
6139  return g_file_new_for_uri (uri);
6140  }
6141  }
6142 
6143  uri_extension = g_strconcat (uri, ".", extensions[0], NULL);
6144  target_file = g_file_new_for_uri (uri_extension);
6145  g_free (uri_extension);
6146  g_strfreev (extensions);
6147 
6148  return target_file;
6149 }

6154  EvWindow *ev_window)
6155 {
6156  GFile *target_file;
6157  gboolean is_native;
6158  GError *error = NULL;
6159  GdkPixbuf *pixbuf;
6160  gchar *uri;
6161  gchar *filename;

6163  GdkPixbufFormat *format;
6164  GtkFileFilter *filter;
6165

6176  format = g_object_get_data (G_OBJECT (filter), "pixbuf-format");
6177 
6178  if (format == NULL) {
6179  format = get_gdk_pixbuf_format_by_extension (uri);
6180  }
6181 
6182  if (format == NULL && g_strrstr (uri, ".") == NULL) {
6183  /* no extension found and no extension provided within uri */
6184  format = get_gdk_pixbuf_format_by_extension (".png");
6185  if (format == NULL) {
6186  /* no .png support, try .jpeg */
6187  format = get_gdk_pixbuf_format_by_extension (".jpeg");

6190

6196  gtk_widget_destroy (fc);
6197 
6198  return;
6199  }
6200 
6201  target_file = create_file_from_uri_for_format (uri, format);
6202  g_free (uri);
6203 
6204  is_native = g_file_is_native (target_file);
6205  if (is_native) {
6206  filename = g_file_get_path (target_file);
6207  } else {
6208  /* Create a temporary local file to save to */
6209  if (ev_mkstemp ("saveimage.XXXXXX", &filename, &error) == -1)
6210  goto has_error;
6211  }
6212 
6213  ev_document_doc_mutex_lock ();
6214  pixbuf = ev_document_images_get_image (EV_DOCUMENT_IMAGES (ev_window->priv->document),
6215  ev_window->priv->image);
6216  ev_document_doc_mutex_unlock ();
6217

6219  gdk_pixbuf_save (pixbuf, filename, file_format, &error, NULL);
6220  g_free (file_format);
6221  g_object_unref (pixbuf);
6222 
6223  has_error:
6224  if (error) {
6225  ev_window_error_message (ev_window, error,
6226  "%s", _("The image could not be saved."));
6227  g_error_free (error);
6228  g_free (filename);
6229  g_object_unref (target_file);
6230  gtk_widget_destroy (fc);
6231 
6232  return;
6233  }
6234 
6235  if (!is_native) {
6236  GFile *source_file;
6237 
6238  source_file = g_file_new_for_path (filename);
6239 
6240  ev_window_save_remote (ev_window, EV_SAVE_IMAGE,
6241  source_file, target_file);
6242  g_object_unref (source_file);
6243  }
6244 
6245  g_free (filename);
6246  g_object_unref (target_file);
6247  gtk_widget_destroy (fc);

6555 static void
6556 ev_window_media_player_key_pressed (EvWindow *window,
6557  const gchar *key,
6558  gpointer user_data)
6559 {
6560  if (!gtk_window_is_active (GTK_WINDOW (window)))
6561  return;
6562 
6563  /* Note how Previous/Next only go to the
6564  * next/previous page despite their icon telling you
6565  * they should go to the beginning/end.
6566  *
6567  * There's very few keyboards with FFW/RWD though,
6568  * so we stick the most useful keybinding on the most
6569  * often seen keys
6570  */
6571  if (strcmp (key, "Play") == 0) {
6572  ev_window_run_presentation (window);
6573  } else if (strcmp (key, "Previous") == 0) {
6574  if (EV_WINDOW_IS_PRESENTATION (window))
6575  ev_view_presentation_previous_page (EV_VIEW_PRESENTATION (window->priv->presentation_view));
6576  else
6577  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "go-previous-page", NULL);
6578  } else if (strcmp (key, "Next") == 0) {
6579  if (EV_WINDOW_IS_PRESENTATION (window))
6580  ev_view_presentation_next_page (EV_VIEW_PRESENTATION (window->priv->presentation_view));
6581  else
6582  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "go-next-page", NULL);
6583  } else if (strcmp (key, "FastForward") == 0) {
6584  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "go-last-page", NULL);
6585  } else if (strcmp (key, "Rewind") == 0) {
6586  g_action_group_activate_action (G_ACTION_GROUP (window), "go-first-page", NULL);
6587  }
6588 }

6644  g_dbus_connection_flush_sync (g_application_get_dbus_connection (g_application_get_default ()), NULL, NULL);

6656 static gboolean
6657 handle_sync_view_cb (EvEvinceWindow *object,
6658  GDBusMethodInvocation *invocation,
6659  const gchar *source_file,
6660  GVariant *source_point,
6661  guint timestamp,
6662  EvWindow *window)
6663 {
6664  if (window->priv->document && ev_document_has_synctex (window->priv->document)) {
6665  EvSourceLink link;
6666 
6667  link.filename = (char *) source_file;
6668  g_variant_get (source_point, "(ii)", &link.line, &link.col);
6669  ev_view_highlight_forward_search (EV_VIEW (window->priv->view), &link);
6670  gtk_window_present_with_time (GTK_WINDOW (window), timestamp);
6671  }
6672 
6673  ev_evince_window_complete_sync_view (object, invocation);
6674 
6675  return TRUE;
6676 }
6677 #endif /* ENABLE_DBUS */

6679 static gboolean
6680 _gtk_css_provider_load_from_resource (GtkCssProvider *provider,
6681  const char *resource_path,
6682  GError **error)
6683 {
6684  GBytes *data;
6685  gboolean retval;
6686 
6687  data = g_resources_lookup_data (resource_path, 0, error);
6688  if (!data)
6689  return FALSE;
6690 
6691  retval = gtk_css_provider_load_from_data (provider,
6692  g_bytes_get_data (data, NULL),
6693  g_bytes_get_size (data),
6694  error);
6695  g_bytes_unref (data);
6696 
6697  return retval;
6698 }
